// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/export/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 7 (façade utility)
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §22 (operational tooling — dump / restore)
//
// Read-only export tooling. Three pieces:
//
//   * `schema_dump` — emit `CREATE TABLE` / `CREATE INDEX` /
//                     `CREATE TRIGGER` / `CREATE VIEW` for every
//                     schema object (mirrors `.schema` in sqlite3 CLI)
//   * `data_dump`   — emit each row as `INSERT INTO ... VALUES (...)`
//                     (matches `.dump`), or as CSV / JSONL
//   * `restore`     — counterpart that consumes the dump back into
//                     a fresh Database
//
// Submodules:
//   * `value`       — abstracted SqlValue + textual rendering
//   * `schema_dump` — schema-object DDL emitter
//   * `data_dump`   — row emitter (INSERT / CSV / JSONL formats)
//   * `restore`     — dump-stream applier
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.export;

public module value;
public module schema_dump;
public module data_dump;
public module restore;
